A **boolean** is a data type that can only be one of two values: `true` or `false`. Booleans are used to make decisions in your code.

```javascript
let isRaining = true;
let isWeekend = false;
let hasLicense = true;
```

blocks.code:
let age = 15;
let hasLicense = false;

console.log(age >= 18 && hasLicense);  // false (both must be true)
console.log(age >= 18 || hasLicense);  // false (at least one must be true)
console.log(!(age >= 18));             // true (flips false to true)
